  "body": "System Information\r\n\r\nGeth version: Geth/v1.10.23-stable-d901d853/linux-amd64/go1.18.5\r\nOS & Version: Debian 11.3 Bullseye\r\n\r\nQuestions:\r\n\r\n1. The `debug_dumpBlock` method is supposed to dump all addresses. Is there any way to get the same information for specific addresses instead? Besides that, it always returns 256 addresses for some reason. Does this method support paging?\r\n\r\n2. The `debug_accountRange` method seems to support paging. What does it expect exactly as the \"start\" parameter? What kind of value is returned as \"next\" in the response? How is the ordering of addresses defined?",
