    "body": "* `debug_dumpBlock` does not support paging. It walks the trie at the block height and spits out every account.\r\n* Does `debug_accountRange(N, addr, 1)` not provide the all the values you need?\r\n* There is a hard-coded limit of 256 results for `debug_dumpBlock`. \r\n* For `debug_accountRange`, the start parameter is the first address in the range. If the address doesn't exist, it will traverse the trie for the next closest address. The third parameter is `maxResults` which declares how many results to return (also capped at 256). You can use those two in concert to provide pagination.\r\n* The ordering of addresses is lexicographical.",
